subSubSection.paragraph:
Male (
Figs. 2–5
). Body length ca. 14.0 mm. Abdominal segments mostly dark brown. Posterior margins of terga 7–9 pale. Tergum 10 with an anterior pair of median sclerites forming an inverted V-shape; a pair of weakly sclerotized triangular spines present on each side of epiproct sclerite, and a pair of blunt, dark projections on posterior margin of tergum 10 lateral to epiproct sclerite. Epiproct sclerite V-shaped, arms thick and apically pointed outwards, base widened and fusiform. Paraprocts long conical, with blunt apices. Sternum 9 with dark brown posterior margin; hammer large, transversely oval, medially with a sparse patch of sensilla basiconica. Aedeagus incompletely everted but entirely membranous, apparently with three finger-shaped apical lobes; dorsal surface with a V-shaped concavity, ventral surface with a narrow median groove.
